resolution: "Latest-state dogfood audit completed with targeted privacy hardening and regression coverage. Telemetry and Sentry scrubbing now redact paths, private-address literals, emails, bearer tokens, and inline credentials; default telemetry capture level is redacted. Core dogfood, SDK/extension docs, calendar, semantic search, CI/CD, health, and tracker hygiene were reviewed and documented."
expected_result: "pm CLI is audited against current tree, verified in an isolated temporary project, privacy leaks are not introduced in tracked files/current item docs, search/calendar/extension/SDK/CI surfaces remain functional, and residual larger hygiene work is tracked without duplicate items."
actual_result: "Implemented telemetry/Sentry redaction hardening, updated docs/changelog/tests, validated temp dogfood lifecycle, hybrid semantic search, calendar markdown output, health/vectorization, security scan, targeted tests, full test suite, and 100% coverage. Created follow-ups pm-xk39 and pm-xz1p for history-stream redaction and legacy linked-file hygiene."
